583
00:27:49.705 --> 00:27:51.025
warning, an ear snap

584
00:27:51.045 --> 00:27:53.625
or a display with no skin, no teeth on skin.

585
00:27:54.435 --> 00:27:57.025
Level two is teeth on skin, but no puncture.

586
00:27:57.045 --> 00:27:58.505
You might see a nick or a scrape.

587
00:27:59.075 --> 00:28:02.065
Level three is one to four punctures from a single bite,

588
00:28:02.415 --> 00:28:04.505
none deeper than half the length of a canine tooth.

589
00:28:04.685 --> 00:28:07.305
You may see a simple tear from someone pulling away.

590
00:28:07.995 --> 00:28:10.905
Level four is more serious, one to four punctures

591
00:28:10.905 --> 00:28:12.785
with at least one deeper than half the canine tooth.

592
00:28:13.235 --> 00:28:15.145
Often there's bruising from a hard grip

593
00:28:15.285 --> 00:28:17.145
and two direction tearing from head shaking.

594
00:28:17.635 --> 00:28:19.745
Level five is a multiple by incident

595
00:28:19.745 --> 00:28:21.545
with at least two level four injuries

596
00:28:21.885 --> 00:28:24.785
or multiple attacks with level four in each level.

597
00:28:24.845 --> 00:28:27.385
Six is fatality. Why does it matter?

